1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available.]

2
00:01:32,770 --> 00:01:34,470
Dad?

3
00:01:57,630 --> 00:01:59,930
Where have you been?

4
00:02:04,270 --> 00:02:07,010
Where were you?

5
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:11,840
My daughter. I’m so sorry.

6
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:15,010
It’s been 12 years.

7
00:02:15,010 --> 00:02:19,350
I’m a grown-up now.

8
00:02:19,350 --> 00:02:22,020
Where were you?

9
00:02:22,020 --> 00:02:23,920
Where?

10
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:29,390
Sorry, my baby girl. I’m so sorry.

11
00:02:29,390 --> 00:02:33,800
How can you do that to me?

12
00:02:38,370 --> 00:02:44,780
You’ve become so old.

13
00:02:44,780 --> 00:02:47,010
How come?

14
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,200
Cheers.

15
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:12,170
Cheers.

16
00:03:12,170 --> 00:03:14,270
You can’t drink alcohol.

17
00:03:14,270 --> 00:03:16,840
Just a little bit.

18
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:19,340
No way.

19
00:03:19,340 --> 00:03:22,450
When it’s snowy, you would buy fried chicken,

20
00:03:22,450 --> 00:03:23,750
and said when I would be old enough

21
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:26,079
to drink alcohol with you.

22
00:03:26,079 --> 00:03:28,750
Now I can even drink a whole barrel!

23
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:29,760
Absurd. You naughty.

24
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:32,520
I mean I’ve grown up.

25
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:37,400
Do you miss me in the past 12 years?

26
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:42,329
I’m glad that you made a name of yourself.

27
00:03:42,329 --> 00:03:45,400
I’m so glad about that.

28
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,970
Because I can see you

29
00:03:47,970 --> 00:03:50,210
on TV, newspapers and movies.

30
00:03:50,210 --> 00:03:52,880
How old is she now?

31
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:56,850
How does she look?

32
00:03:56,850 --> 00:03:58,680
I can see you every day.

33
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:01,150
What about me?

34
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:04,290
I can’t see you.

35
00:04:04,290 --> 00:04:10,430
I don’t even know if you’re still alive.

36
00:04:10,430 --> 00:04:12,860
My former manager’s dad

37
00:04:12,860 --> 00:04:14,700
was so sick that he depended on

38
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:18,670
a breathing machine in hospital for years.

39
00:04:18,670 --> 00:04:21,910
I even envy that.

40
00:04:21,910 --> 00:04:27,780
As long as you’re alive and with me,

41
00:04:27,780 --> 00:04:33,620
I just want you to be with me.

42
00:04:33,620 --> 00:04:35,820
I mean it.

43
00:04:35,820 --> 00:04:37,420
Do you ever hate me?

44
00:04:37,420 --> 00:04:40,360
You don’t know me?

45
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:44,960
I’ll regret it every time I get angry.

46
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:49,870
I ran out that day and nearly had an accident.

47
00:04:49,870 --> 00:04:54,010
I was thinking that I need to tell you this.

48
00:04:54,010 --> 00:05:00,610
A man saved me from an accident.
I wanted to tell you…

49
00:05:00,610 --> 00:05:05,320
But you were gone when I was back.

50
00:05:09,620 --> 00:05:10,960
I’m sorry.

51
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:13,160
Enough.

52
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:15,630
Thank you for not leaving me alone

53
00:05:15,630 --> 00:05:19,160
after the surgery.

54
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:26,270
The grudge I’ve been holding
for 12 years is gone.

55
00:05:31,810 --> 00:05:36,380
But dad, do you have a new family?

56
00:05:36,380 --> 00:05:40,750
Do I have siblings?

57
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:45,220
Nonsense!

58
00:05:50,130 --> 00:05:52,030
What?

59
00:05:52,030 --> 00:05:55,730
You never dated anyone?

60
00:05:55,730 --> 00:05:58,400
And you? Do you have a boyfriend?

61
00:05:59,970 --> 00:06:01,570
No.

62
00:06:01,570 --> 00:06:02,840
I don’t have one.

63
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:04,540
It’s true!

64
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:09,550
I’m like my mom, who’s picky about men.

65
00:06:09,550 --> 00:06:12,820
I haven’t met a man who’s as good as you are.

66
00:06:12,820 --> 00:06:15,020
You silly! Never do that!

67
00:06:15,020 --> 00:06:18,260
A guy like me will be a disaster.

68
00:06:18,260 --> 00:06:20,790
Really?

69
00:06:20,790 --> 00:06:27,870
Right. If he leaves me alone like you did,

70
00:06:27,870 --> 00:06:34,310
I would be so upset.

71
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:37,440
But it’s over.

72
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:40,110
He will never like me back.

73
00:06:42,780 --> 00:06:45,380
What?

74
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:47,990
I don’t know who he is.

75
00:06:47,990 --> 00:06:49,520
But you’ll be loved by someone.

76
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:51,560
No one knows you better than I do.

77
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:53,860
That guy must like you so much.

78
00:06:53,860 --> 00:06:56,930
Stop talking about it. You know nothing.

79
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:01,470
I find that

80
00:07:01,470 --> 00:07:05,570
it’s not easy to be liked back

81
00:07:05,570 --> 00:07:08,440
by the one I like.

82
00:07:10,810 --> 00:07:16,450
If so, that’s miracle.

83
00:07:40,170 --> 00:07:43,940
[Last month on Earth.]

84
00:08:00,330 --> 00:08:03,630
[My Love from the Star Record 15]

85
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:12,700
Stop it.

86
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:19,240
I’m sure there must be a secret way out.

87
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,110
Not the door?

88
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:28,690
The wall, either.

89
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:41,270
Mr. Do… Do Min-joon?

90
00:08:42,169 --> 00:08:47,640
You had some emergency, right?

91
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:51,080
I’m sorry about that.

92
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:54,380
I need to make it clear this time.

93
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:58,520
Okay. Go ahead.

94
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:04,860
But what I am telling you is totally different.

95
00:09:04,860 --> 00:09:07,660
Maybe even unbelievable.

96
00:09:10,260 --> 00:09:14,300
Can we talk at somewhere without CCTV?

97
00:09:15,870 --> 00:09:17,500
Why?

98
00:09:22,470 --> 00:09:25,540
What have we heard?

99
00:09:29,350 --> 00:09:34,690
That day, I did go to the cruise.

100
00:09:34,690 --> 00:09:39,990
Why were you filmed
by the CCTV at the apartment?

101
00:09:39,990 --> 00:09:41,660
Because...

102
00:09:43,730 --> 00:09:46,700
I can do teleportation.

103
00:09:54,310 --> 00:09:58,740
Dude. Are you kidding with the civil servants?

104
00:09:58,740 --> 00:09:59,780
Cut it out.

105
00:09:59,780 --> 00:10:01,450
Please go on.

106
00:10:01,450 --> 00:10:06,750
I think I need to tell you who I really am

107
00:10:06,750 --> 00:10:11,760
or you’ll never believe what I’m going to say.

108
00:10:12,620 --> 00:10:16,090
The reason I can’t make public

109
00:10:16,090 --> 00:10:20,930
is the secret I have to keep.

110
00:10:20,930 --> 00:10:26,640
I heard what the murderer
who killed Han Yoo-ra said.

111
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:29,880
I don’t know what it meant at that time.

112
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:33,410
But later I found that it’s related to that case.

113
00:10:33,410 --> 00:10:35,850
Who’s that guy?

114
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:41,920
Director of S&C Group, Lee Jae-kyung.

115
00:10:45,460 --> 00:10:48,260
Do you have evidence?

116
00:10:55,230 --> 00:11:00,140
Miss Han Yoo-ra’s USB has the video of them.

117
00:11:00,140 --> 00:11:03,680
But that USB prevents any replication.

118
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:07,950
And this one has reshot the video.

119
00:11:07,950 --> 00:11:12,050
Does it have the decisive evidence
of Han Yoo-ra’s case?

120
00:11:12,050 --> 00:11:13,720
Not exactly.

121
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:17,690
But it has the proof that they were dating.

122
00:11:17,690 --> 00:11:19,960
Han Yoo-ra knows Lee Jea-kyung’s weakness.

123
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:24,430
She took it to force him to get married.

124
00:11:24,430 --> 00:11:28,200
Please dig into it with this USB.

125
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,870
As long as you believe me,

126
00:11:30,870 --> 00:11:36,240
I’ll provide my best help in the coming month.

127
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:44,620
Do you buy it? Teleportation?

128
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:53,830
What nonsense.

129
00:11:53,830 --> 00:11:56,460
Do you buy it?

130
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:59,430
I think you were quite calm.

131
00:11:59,430 --> 00:12:03,240
I’m not sure.

132
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:05,870
But what I can be sure of

133
00:12:05,870 --> 00:12:10,240
is that Do Min-joon is not a common person

134
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:13,650
This is freaking me out.

135
00:12:13,650 --> 00:12:19,650
I don’t buy it in my mind, but I somewhat

136
00:12:19,650 --> 00:12:21,590
believe it in my heart.

137
00:12:21,590 --> 00:12:26,120
Since when do I ever believed Do Min-joon?

138
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:28,960
This elusive man!

139
00:12:33,770 --> 00:12:36,940
I bought this for you. Try it.

140
00:12:36,940 --> 00:12:39,770
It’s okay. You can have it.

141
00:12:44,610 --> 00:12:47,180
You’re waiting for someone?

142
00:12:47,180 --> 00:12:49,450
I’m not.

143
00:12:49,450 --> 00:12:53,250
I found your disappointed look when I entered.

144
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:56,660
You’re waiting for his call, right?

145
00:12:56,660 --> 00:13:00,660
Someone doesn’t know I’m in hospital?

146
00:13:00,660 --> 00:13:02,090
I don’t think so.

147
00:13:02,090 --> 00:13:04,160
I think the entire country knows it.

148
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:08,900
You’re the spotlight of all over Asia.

149
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:12,340
Even the dogs in my neighborhood know it.

150
00:13:12,340 --> 00:13:14,170
Your fans are everywhere.

151
00:13:14,170 --> 00:13:17,340
But if someone has no access to the Internet,
he might not know it, right?

152
00:13:17,340 --> 00:13:18,880
Who is it?

153
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:19,710
An alien?

154
00:13:19,710 --> 00:13:22,550
Hey. Hush!

155
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:24,420
You crazy?

156
00:13:24,420 --> 00:13:26,080
You!

157
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:30,090
Do you think that guy is an alien?

158
00:13:30,090 --> 00:13:33,560
No...

159
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:37,860
And you know what, this is ridiculous.

160
00:13:37,860 --> 00:13:39,830
You can’t do that.

161
00:13:39,830 --> 00:13:40,730
What did I do?

162
00:13:40,730 --> 00:13:45,940
Hee-kyung is in a coma because of you.

163
00:13:45,940 --> 00:13:47,670
And you’re thinking of another man.

164
00:13:47,670 --> 00:13:49,810
This is ridiculous.

165
00:13:49,810 --> 00:13:55,150
If it were not Hee-kyung, you’d have been dead!

166
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:59,550
He ended up like this to save your life.

167
00:13:59,550 --> 00:14:01,420
That alien or ghost man

168
00:14:01,420 --> 00:14:04,590
disappeared when you needed help.

169
00:14:04,590 --> 00:14:07,630
He said he hates you, right?

170
00:14:07,630 --> 00:14:10,160
Does he?

171
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:11,830
It was random talks.

172
00:14:11,830 --> 00:14:15,230
Men talk in different ways with women.

173
00:14:15,230 --> 00:14:18,570
A woman may not mean it
when she says she hate you.

174
00:14:18,570 --> 00:14:21,070
But when a man says so,

175
00:14:21,070 --> 00:14:23,010
he really means it.

176
00:14:23,010 --> 00:14:25,580
He hate you for sure.

177
00:14:25,580 --> 00:14:28,480
Forget that alien this time.

178
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:31,980
Make some progress with Hee-Kyung.

179
00:14:31,980 --> 00:14:33,720
This is what you should do.

180
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:35,250
Stop waiting for him.

181
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:36,420
I’m not!

182
00:14:36,420 --> 00:14:38,620
I’m not waiting.

183
00:15:17,630 --> 00:15:19,830
I need to go home.

184
00:15:34,680 --> 00:15:37,050
Is he getting better?

185
00:15:37,050 --> 00:15:39,750
It’s said the surgery went well. How...

186
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:43,560
No need to worry. He’ll be fine soon.

187
00:15:44,860 --> 00:15:47,530
If it hadn’t been him, I’d have been dead.

188
00:15:47,530 --> 00:15:51,200
Yeah. I heard that.

189
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:23,900
Oh, right.

190
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:28,530
Did the police officers come to you?

191
00:16:28,530 --> 00:16:30,040
They did.

192
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:34,870
I was interrogated by him.

193
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:40,050
He mistook others as Yoo-ra’s boyfriend.

194
00:16:40,050 --> 00:16:42,050
So I told him

195
00:16:42,050 --> 00:16:45,150
that you are Yoo-ra’s boyfriend.

196
00:16:45,150 --> 00:16:46,850
I know.

197
00:16:46,850 --> 00:16:51,490
Do I get you in trouble?

198
00:16:51,490 --> 00:16:54,030
I think you misunderstand us.

199
00:16:54,030 --> 00:16:59,460
We’re not that relationship.

200
00:16:59,460 --> 00:17:04,069
I can’t distain a late friend’s name,
so I can’t tell you more.

201
00:17:04,069 --> 00:17:07,240
Oh, I see.

202
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:10,609
I believed in what I saw.

203
00:17:10,609 --> 00:17:13,250
so I might tell the police something useless.

204
00:17:14,280 --> 00:17:20,950
Do you tell anyone else except for that police?

205
00:17:24,060 --> 00:17:26,119
I told Hee-kyung about it.

206
00:17:26,119 --> 00:17:30,160
Oh, I see.

207
00:18:07,970 --> 00:18:09,300
[Cheon Song-yi’s boyfriend is a rich guy.]

208
00:18:12,940 --> 00:18:14,910
Gosh. Did you see that?

209
00:18:14,910 --> 00:18:18,140
Cheon Song-yi was caught by a man in the scene.

210
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:19,410
And he is super rich!

211
00:18:19,410 --> 00:18:21,210
Awesome!

212
00:18:21,210 --> 00:18:23,250
We have such a rich and handsome man?

213
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:24,750
She’s so lucky. She always can make it.

214
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:28,820
A rich and handsome bachelor saved her life.

215
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:35,760
I can’t contact Mr. Lee Jea-Kyung.

216
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:39,500
I’m afraid I have to breach the contract.

217
00:18:39,500 --> 00:18:42,000
My girl will leave the hospital tomorrow.

218
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:46,410
I can’t sign the contract without her consent.

219
00:18:46,410 --> 00:18:48,440
Did you tell him that?

220
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:52,380
I did. But he disagreed.

221
00:18:52,380 --> 00:18:53,650
Disagreed?

222
00:18:53,650 --> 00:18:55,680
Why? I’ll return the contract amount.

223
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:57,450
Please review the contract.

224
00:18:57,450 --> 00:19:01,050
It requires 3 times of the amount.

225
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:09,230
We’re acquaintances. How can he?

226
00:19:09,230 --> 00:19:12,230
I have to talk to Mr. Lee Jae-kyung.

227
00:19:12,230 --> 00:19:13,770
Where is he?

228
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:18,300
I’ll call you back.

229
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:27,780
Excuse me? Were you saying Mr. Lee Jae-kyung?

230
00:19:27,780 --> 00:19:28,980
I was. Mr. Do Min-joon.

231
00:19:28,980 --> 00:19:31,050
It’s him. So what?

232
00:19:31,050 --> 00:19:32,150
You haven’t been updated?

233
00:19:32,150 --> 00:19:37,290
Song-yi has signed a contract with him.

234
00:19:38,190 --> 00:19:42,460
He’ll cover all the limousines and managers.

235
00:19:42,460 --> 00:19:44,730
Has Song-yi agreed to it?

236
00:19:44,730 --> 00:19:46,030
What?

237
00:19:46,930 --> 00:19:49,200
She hasn’t.

238
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:50,770
Just drop it for now.

239
00:19:50,770 --> 00:19:54,440
I have a question for you.

240
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:55,970
Who do you think you are?

241
00:19:55,970 --> 00:19:57,440
Excuse me?

242
00:19:57,440 --> 00:19:59,610
Are you blind?

243
00:19:59,610 --> 00:20:01,710
My daughter is Cheon Song-yi!

244
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:04,780
How dare you refuse her?

245
00:20:04,780 --> 00:20:08,220
Excuse me. You’re being unreasonable.

246
00:20:08,220 --> 00:20:09,490
What do you mean by that?

247
00:20:09,490 --> 00:20:11,760
And you are?

248
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:14,560
I’m his father.

249
00:20:14,560 --> 00:20:16,060
So what?

250
00:20:16,060 --> 00:20:16,600
Well...

251
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:18,500
My daughter is Cheon Song-yi.

252
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:21,200
She’s the dream girl of all men.

253
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:23,870
Every man wants to date her.

254
00:20:23,870 --> 00:20:26,240
Are you serious?

255
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:29,410
Min-joon went to Harvard.

256
00:20:29,410 --> 00:20:34,080
And as you can see, he’s a handsome gentleman.

257
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:34,610
Dad.

258
00:20:34,610 --> 00:20:37,350
He’s my treasure.

259
00:20:37,350 --> 00:20:38,880
What does it help even if he went to Harvard?

260
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:41,090
He’s so irresponsible.

261
00:20:41,090 --> 00:20:44,690
You should have stuck to being her manager.

262
00:20:44,690 --> 00:20:46,490
Oh, the manager.

263
00:20:46,490 --> 00:20:48,960
He didn’t ask for it.

264
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:52,360
It was your daughter who begged him to be.

265
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:53,170
That’s enough.

266
00:20:53,170 --> 00:20:55,300
That’s not enough. You silly boy.

267
00:20:55,300 --> 00:20:56,970
What is going on here?

268
00:20:56,970 --> 00:20:58,840
I told you not to do so.

269
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:01,140
Are you lack of money or are you bored?

270
00:21:01,140 --> 00:21:04,580
How could you be her manager?

271
00:21:04,580 --> 00:21:07,750
Alas. This is absurd.

272
00:21:07,750 --> 00:21:10,750
Everyone in this world wants to be her manager.

273
00:21:10,750 --> 00:21:14,820
Then just pick one!

274
00:21:14,820 --> 00:21:16,250
Let’s get in.

275
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:17,890
